n I used to occasionally hang out there with my old classmate, the late <st=
rong>John F. Kennedy Jr. </strong>I enjoyed meeting so many of you from the=
 banking world and catching up with my friend <strong>Meredith Whitney</str=
ong>, the unparalleled research analyst (and loyal Puck
subscriber), among many others.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"=
>=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Today, I=E2=80=99ve got=
 a tale of how artificial intelligence is starting to disrupt Wall Street=
=E2=80=94and a new player in the space that may reap a fortune from the tra=
nsition. As my pal <strong>Scott Galloway</strong> has noted, A.I. is not a=
bout to replace bankers <em>per se</em>, but it <em>is</em> going to replac=
e the bankers who aren=E2=80=99t using it.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
